snippet.textDisplay:
I disagree with some of what this doctor says, but he does seem knowledgeable. He says it's a myth that corona is an old person's disease. Rogan asks him is that a myth because it's mostly old people that have died from it? Doctor says yes. LOL.... myth confirmed. It's not that this virus is 15x "worse" than a flu, it's that some people (elderly, immune compromised, fat, or some other lung issue) develop a complication in which too much fluid is produced in their lungs, and they die from that. If you are one of the vast majority of people who don't develop that complication, you will not die from this disease.
I do agree with the doctor when he says it's not just the disease, but what it does to the system. THAT is what I'm worried about. Fuck the virus. I'm worried they are literally going to shut down all of society because of it. Ridiculous. It is inevitable that the virus is going to spread anyway. I think it would be better to not be so insane about shutting everything down. I might change that sentiment if it were actually a more severe virus, but only a small percentage of people die, so..... let's not wreck everything for a small number like that. And also, they are saying now the spread is inevitable anyway. So what's with the insane futile measures of trying to stop it?
